						<summary>

						<p>Slab lying in the compound of Śiva temple.</p>						

						<p>Kāyastha: Tripurāridēva.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1226, Krōdhi, Chaitra śu. 7, Thursday</hi> corresponding to 1304 A.D., March 14. However the weekday is Saturday.</p>						

						<p>It records the gift of the village Varikuṇṭa situated in Sakali along with incomes such as <hi rend="italic">aḍḍasunkam ashṭāyas</hi> as <hi rend="italic">sarvamānya</hi> to the god Siddhanāthadēva for the maintenance of the worship and daily offerings to the god by the king Tripurāridēva, son of Ambadēva Mahārāju and also gift of land to the same god.</p>						

						</summary>
